```markdown
# Site Inspector - Blazor PWA for Construction Inspectors

## Architecture
- **Blazor Web App** with Interactive WebAssembly (global mode)
- **Offline-first PWA** with IndexedDB storage and service worker caching
- **Two projects**: Server (`SiteInspector`) and Client (`SiteInspector.Client`)

## Key Design Decisions
- All UI logic runs in WebAssembly for offline capability
- IndexedDB via JS interop stores all data locally
- Sync queue pattern: all changes go to IndexedDB first, then sync when online
- Mobile-first CSS with large touch targets (44px minimum)
- No authentication required

## Building
```bash
dotnet build SiteInspector.sln
```

## Project Structure
- `SiteInspector/` - Server project (hosts WASM, API endpoints, static files)
- `SiteInspector.Client/` - Client WASM project (UI, services, models)
- Models are in `SiteInspector.Client/Models/`
- Services are in `SiteInspector.Client/Services/`
- Pages are in `SiteInspector.Client/Pages/`
- IndexedDB JS interop is in `SiteInspector.Client/wwwroot/js/indexedDb.js`

## Sync Flow
1. User makes changes → saved to IndexedDB immediately
2. Change added to `syncQueue` store
3. SyncService polls every 30s when online
4. Pending items sent as batch to `POST /api/sync`
5. On success, items marked as synced

## Adding New Checklist Categories
Edit `InspectionDataService.CreateDefaultChecklist()` in `Services/InspectionDataService.cs`
